   "source": [
    "# Notebook 2 — Modélisation & Sélection du Meilleur Modèle\n",
    "**Projet L3 Data Science — Système de Détection Précoce des Étudiants en Difficulté**\n",
    "\n",
    "Équipe : Anta NGOM, Mohamadou Yaya BALARABE, Pape M. K. DIAW, Mohamed B. DIAKHATE, Bazoungoula Lasie-Havila  \n",
    "Superviseur : Dr. Seydou Nourou SYLLA\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "**Objectif :** Entraîner et comparer trois algorithmes via GridSearchCV, sélectionner le meilleur modèle selon le **F1-score sur la classe Ajourné** (équilibre Recall/Précision), puis exporter `model.joblib` pour Flask.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Choix du critère de sélection\n",
    "Le scoring est le **F1 sur la classe 1 (Ajourné)**, pas le Recall seul.  \n",
    "Scorer uniquement sur le Recall pousse le modèle à prédire tout le monde comme \"Ajourné\" (Recall trivial = 1.0), ce qui est inutile en production.  \n",
    "Le F1 impose un **équilibre entre détecter les ajournés (Recall) et ne pas faussement alarmer les bons étudiants (Précision)**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import joblib\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, GridSearchCV, StratifiedKFold, cross_val_score\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
    "    classification_report, confusion_matrix,\n",
    "    recall_score, precision_score, accuracy_score, f1_score,\n",
    "    roc_auc_score, roc_curve, ConfusionMatrixDisplay, make_scorer\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', palette='muted')\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 100\n",
    "\n",
    "RANDOM_STATE = 42"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Chargement du Dataset Propre"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Dataset : 1000 étudiants | 4 features\n",
      "Cible   : {0: 838, 1: 162} (0=Admis, 1=Ajourné)\n",
      "Taux d'ajournement : 16.2%\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_csv('dataset_propre.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "# 4 features S1 : les 3 brutes + le score_s1 synthétique\n",
    "FEATURES = ['heures_etude_hebdo', 'taux_presence_S1', 'note_TD_S1', 'score_s1']\n",
    "TARGET   = 'statut_ajourne'\n",
    "\n",
    "X = df[FEATURES]\n",
    "y = df[TARGET]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset : {X.shape[0]} étudiants | {X.shape[1]} features\")\n",
    "print(f\"Cible   : {y.value_counts().to_dict()} (0=Admis, 1=Ajourné)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Taux d'ajournement : {y.mean()*100:.1f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Split Train / Test Stratifié"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Train : 800 | Test : 200\n",
      "Proportion ajournés — Train : 16.25% | Test : 16.00%\n",
      "✅ Stratify=y garantit la même proportion d'ajournés dans les deux blocs.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, stratify=y\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Train : {X_train.shape[0]} | Test : {X_test.shape[0]}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Proportion ajournés — Train : {y_train.mean():.2%} | Test : {y_test.mean():.2%}\")\n",
    "print(\"✅ Stratify=y garantit la même proportion d'ajournés dans les deux blocs.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. GridSearchCV avec Pipelines\n",
    "\n",
    "Chaque modèle est encapsulé dans un **Pipeline (StandardScaler → Modèle)** pour éviter toute fuite de données entre les folds de validation croisée.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Scoring : F1 sur la classe 1 (Ajourné)**  \n",
    "Ce scorer exige du modèle qu'il détecte les ajournés (Recall) **et** qu'il ne sur-prédicte pas les échecs (Précision). `class_weight='balanced'` est exploré pour corriger automatiquement le déséquilibre des classes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "GridSearchCV lancé (scoring = F1 classe Ajourné)...\n",
      "\n",
      "▶  Régression Logistique\n",
      "   Meilleurs paramètres : {'clf__C': 1, 'clf__class_weight': None, 'clf__solver': 'liblinear'}\n",
      "   F1 CV (train)        : 0.8493\n",
      "   Recall   (test)      : 0.9062  ← Ajournés détectés\n",
      "   Précision (test)     : 0.8286  ← Fausses alertes\n",
      "   F1       (test)      : 0.8657\n",
      "   Accuracy (test)      : 0.9550\n",
      "\n",
      "▶  Arbre de Décision\n",
      "   Meilleurs paramètres : {'clf__class_weight': 'balanced', 'clf__criterion': 'entropy', 'clf__max_depth': None, 'clf__min_samples_leaf': 5}\n",
      "   F1 CV (train)        : 0.8466\n",
      "   Recall   (test)      : 0.9375  ← Ajournés détectés\n",
      "   Précision (test)     : 0.7317  ← Fausses alertes\n",
      "   F1       (test)      : 0.8219\n",
      "   Accuracy (test)      : 0.9350\n",
      "\n",
      "▶  Forêt Aléatoire\n",
      "   Meilleurs paramètres : {'clf__class_weight': None, 'clf__max_depth': 8, 'clf__min_samples_leaf': 4, 'clf__n_estimators': 100}\n",
      "   F1 CV (train)        : 0.8406\n",
      "   Recall   (test)      : 0.7812  ← Ajournés détectés\n",
      "   Précision (test)     : 0.8333  ← Fausses alertes\n",
      "   F1       (test)      : 0.8065\n",
      "   Accuracy (test)      : 0.9400\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "cv = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=RANDOM_STATE)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scorer personnalisé : F1 sur la classe Ajourné (pos_label=1)\n",
    "scorer_f1_ajourne = make_scorer(f1_score, pos_label=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "search_configs = {\n",
    "    'Régression Logistique': {\n",
    "        'pipeline': Pipeline([\n",
    "            ('scaler', StandardScaler()),\n",
    "            ('clf', LogisticRegression(random_state=RANDOM_STATE, max_iter=1000))\n",
    "        ]),\n",
    "        'params': {\n",
    "            'clf__C'           : [0.01, 0.1, 1, 10, 100],\n",
    "            'clf__class_weight': [None, 'balanced'],\n",
    "            'clf__solver'      : ['lbfgs', 'liblinear']\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    'Arbre de Décision': {\n",
    "        'pipeline': Pipeline([\n",
    "            ('scaler', StandardScaler()),\n",
    "            ('clf', DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=RANDOM_STATE))\n",
    "        ]),\n",
    "        'params': {\n",
    "            'clf__max_depth'        : [3, 4, 5, 6, None],\n",
    "            'clf__min_samples_leaf' : [1, 3, 5],\n",
    "            'clf__criterion'        : ['gini', 'entropy'],\n",
    "            'clf__class_weight'     : [None, 'balanced']\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    'Forêt Aléatoire': {\n",
    "        'pipeline': Pipeline([\n",
    "            ('scaler', StandardScaler()),\n",
    "            ('clf', RandomForestClassifier(random_state=RANDOM_STATE))\n",
    "        ]),\n",
    "        'params': {\n",
    "            'clf__n_estimators'     : [100, 200],\n",
    "            'clf__max_depth'        : [4, 6, 8, None],\n",
    "            'clf__min_samples_leaf' : [1, 2, 4],\n",
    "            'clf__class_weight'     : [None, 'balanced']\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"GridSearchCV lancé (scoring = F1 classe Ajourné)...\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "results = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for nom, config in search_configs.items():\n",
    "    gs = GridSearchCV(\n",
    "        estimator  = config['pipeline'],\n",
    "        param_grid = config['params'],\n",
    "        scoring    = scorer_f1_ajourne,\n",
    "        cv         = cv,\n",
    "        n_jobs     = -1,\n",
    "        refit      = True\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    gs.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "    results[nom] = gs\n",
    "\n",
    "    y_pred = gs.predict(X_test)\n",
    "    print(f\"▶  {nom}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Meilleurs paramètres : {gs.best_params_}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   F1 CV (train)        : {gs.best_score_:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Recall   (test)      : {recall_score(y_test, y_pred):.4f}  ← Ajournés détectés\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Précision (test)     : {precision_score(y_test, y_pred):.4f}  ← Fausses alertes\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   F1       (test)      : {f1_score(y_test, y_pred):.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Accuracy (test)      : {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred):.4f}\")\n",
    "    print()"
   ]
  },
